 be glad to enter into an agreement with you concerning a translation (with a few commentaries essential for students) of Anna Karenin. It would be based in the main on the Garnett version, with all the blunders corrected, and with all the images and special Tolstoyan locutions faithfully restored. Let me know your reaction to this plan.

